[center][size=5][b]LockpickSettings[/b][/size]
[i]Your toolbox for the lockpicking minigame: more tries, an optional next-move hint, fully configurable.[/i][/center]
[line]
[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]

[quote][size=4][b]🔒 More Tries[/b][/size]

Your lockpick durability (failed attempts before the pick breaks) is raised from the vanilla value of your Picklock skill tier to vanilla + 10:

[list]
[*][b]Untrained:[/b] 2 -> 12 tries
[*][b]Trained:[/b] 4 -> 14 tries
[*][b]Master:[/b] 6 -> 16 tries
[/list]

Every tier gets the same bonus, so learning the skill still matters. Both the bonus and the per-tier vanilla values are configurable.[/quote]

[quote][size=4][b]💡 Next-Move Hint[/b] [i](optional, off by default)[/i][/size]

Press [b]F7[/b] during the lockpicking minigame and the piece you should move next lights up, [color=#66ff66][b]green[/b][/color] when the correct turn is [b]LEFT[/b], [color=#5e9eff][b]blue[/b][/color] when it is [b]RIGHT[/b], recomputed after every move from the lock's live state. Follow the colors and the lock opens on the shortest path.

[list]
[*]Toggle it any time, even mid-pick: the mod follows every lock from its start, the key only switches the highlight.
[*]Works identically with keyboard and controller.
[*]The direction colors calibrate themselves from your first move, so they are exact for every lock and camera angle.
[*]The lock connection layouts ship with the mod, extracted from the game's own data files for all 416 locks; positions are measured live (the game re-scrambles them per attempt).
[*]The game removes some connections at runtime depending on your skill; the mod detects that from your moves and adapts, so a hint can occasionally lag one move behind.
[*]The master perk (removing connections when a pick breaks) keeps its full value.
[/list][/quote]

[quote][size=4][b]🔗 Connection Display[/b] [i](optional, off by default)[/i][/size]

Press [b]F8[/b] during the lockpicking minigame and the pieces connected to your currently SELECTED piece light up, direction-coded: [color=#b366ff][b]purple[/b][/color] when a piece travels the [b]SAME[/b] direction as the selected one, [color=#ff5555][b]red[/b][/color] when it travels [b]OPPOSITE[/b]. Selection tracking works with keyboard and controller and re-anchors itself on every actual move. Both colors are configurable, and the next-move hint always outranks them on the hinted piece.

[b]Honest caveat:[/b] the display shows the authored lock layout. The game silently deactivates some connections at runtime (depending on your skill, and the master perk removes more when a pick breaks), and the mod cannot see that directly: a deactivated connection keeps showing until one of your moves disproves it, at which point it is pruned for the rest of that attempt. So treat the colors as "may drag", not "will drag"; they become exact as you play the lock.[/quote]

[size=4][b]Planned[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Reduction of connections:[/b] genuinely simpler locks, without exchanging original lock layouts and without changing base character stats.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[url=https://github.com/UE4SS-RE/RE-UE4SS]UE4SS[/url] in an experimental build. The game runs Unreal Engine 5.4.3, which the stable UE4SS 3.0.1 release predates, so download the [b]experimental-latest[/b] release:
[url=https://github.com/UE4SS-RE/RE-UE4SS/releases/tag/experimental-latest]https://github.com/UE4SS-RE/RE-UE4SS/releases/tag/experimental-latest[/url]
Grab the regular UE4SS zip, not the zDEV developer package.

Note: experimental-latest is a moving tag. This mod is developed and tested against the build identified as [b]v3.0.1 Beta, Git SHA e09d3821[/b] (v4.0.0-rc1 line) in the first lines of UE4SS.log. If you see strange script errors with a different snapshot, that version difference is the first suspect.

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[list=1]
[*]Extract the UE4SS zip into [b]...\Gothic 1 Remake\G1R\Binaries\Win64[/b], so that dwmapi.dll sits next to G1R-Win64-Shipping.exe and a ue4ss folder appears beside it.
[*]Extract the LockpickSettings zip from this page into [b]...\G1R\Binaries\Win64\ue4ss\Mods[/b]. You should end up with:
[code]...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\enabled.txt
...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\Scripts\main.lua
...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\Scripts\config.lua
...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\Scripts\lockgraphs.lua[/code]
The included enabled.txt activates the mod automatically; you do NOT need to edit mods.txt.
[*]Start the game. [b]...\ue4ss\UE4SS.log[/b] should now contain:
[code][LockpickSettings] Loaded: untrained 2->12, trained 4->14, master 6->16, next-move hint off (416 lock graphs, toggle: F7), connection display off, toggle: F8[/code]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

Edit [b]...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\Scripts\config.lua[/b]:

[list]
[*][b]extraTries[/b]: the bonus added on top of the vanilla tries (default 10)
[*][b]baseTries[/b]: the vanilla tries per skill tier; only touch these if a game patch changes them
[*][b]showNextMove[/b]: whether the next-move hint is active at game start (default false)
[*][b]nextMoveHotkey[/b]: the key that toggles the hint ingame (default "F7", "" disables the hotkey)
[*][b]hintColorLeft[/b] / [b]hintColorRight[/b]: the hint colors as {r, g, b}, encoding which way to turn the hinted lock (defaults: green = left, blue = right; set both equal for a directionless hint)
[*][b]showConnections[/b]: whether the connection display is active at game start (default false)
[*][b]connectionsHotkey[/b]: the key that toggles the connection display (default "F8", "" disables)
[*][b]partnerColorSame[/b] / [b]partnerColorOpposite[/b]: the connected-pieces colors as {r, g, b}, by drag direction relative to the selected piece (defaults: purple = same, red = opposite)
[*][b]debugSolver[/b]: verbose solver logging for bug reports (default false)
[/list]

Apply changes with a game restart or CTRL+R ingame (UE4SS hot reload).

[size=4][b]How it works, safety[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]A single UE4SS Lua callback fires when the lockpicking minigame starts and adjusts the LockpickDurability attribute on the player. No game files are modified, nothing is patched on disk.
[*]The durability value itself identifies your skill tier: vanilla values get raised, already raised values are recognized and left alone. Nothing can stack or run away across sessions and saves.
[*]The next-move hint reads the lock's live state from the game's material parameter collection a few times per second, only while a minigame is open, and computes the shortest solution with a small search. It tints pieces via a material parameter; nothing else is touched.
[*]The assists listen READ-ONLY to the minigame's own input events (to track your selection and calibrate the hint colors). Nothing is intercepted, blocked or modified; your inputs reach the game untouched.
[*]Uninstalling returns lockpicking to vanilla behavior; the game rebuilds the stat from your skill tier when a save loads.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Troubleshooting[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]No log lines / mod not loading:[/b] check the folder layout (exactly as shown above, with enabled.txt directly inside the LockpickSettings folder).
[*][b]"durability X not a known tier" in the log:[/b] a game patch changed the vanilla values; update baseTries in config.lua.
[*][b]"No graph data for lock" in the log:[/b] that lock is not in the shipped data (one lock in the game has none, and future patches may add locks); the hint stays off for it, everything else works.
[*][b]Game hard-freezes when loading a save, or crashes/strange script errors during lockpicking:[/b] some UE4SS engine hooks can collide with this game's AngelScript layer and corrupt the process (the mod's own errors are caught and only disable the hint until the next lock; they never crash the game by themselves). The mod needs none of those hooks, so you can safely turn them off in ue4ss\UE4SS-settings.ini: set HookProcessInternal, HookProcessLocalScriptFunction, HookUObjectProcessEvent, HookCallFunctionByNameWithArguments and HookAActorTick to 0, and bUseUObjectArrayCache to false. Also check that your UE4SS build matches the tested one (see Requirements).
[*][b]Access violation when quitting the game:[/b] known cosmetic UE4SS teardown issue, happens after everything has been saved. Harmless.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Source[/b][/size]

Lua source, the lock-data extractor and dev notes: [url=https://github.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods]github.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods[/url]
